Description: iRFP720 is a basic (constitutively fluorescent) near ir fluorescent protein published in 2013, derived from Rhodopseudomonas palustris. It has low acid sensitivity. It requires the cofactor biliverdin for fluorescence.
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
chloramphenicol acetyltransferase; cat; confers resistance to chloramphenicol
pdk; modified pyruvate orthophosphate dikinase intron from Flaveria trinervia 3.0
lac repressor; lacI; The lac repressor binds to the lac operator to inhibit transcription in E. coli. This inhibition can be relieved by adding lactose or isopropyl-β-D-thiogalactopyranoside (IPTG).
